<list1 type="nonmark">
<item>
<ptxt>*<sup>1</sup>: If the room temperature is approx. -18.6°C (-1.48°F) or lower, DTC B1411/11 may be output even though the system is normal.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>*<sup>2</sup>: If the ambient temperature is approx. -52.9°C (-63.22°F) or lower, DTC B1412/12 may be output even though the system is normal.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>*<sup>3</sup>: If the check is performed in a dark place, DTC B1421/21 or B1424/24 (solar sensor circuit abnormal) may be output even though the system is normal.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>*<sup>4</sup>: The A/C amplifier memorizes the DTC of the respective malfunction if it has occurred for the period of time indicated in the brackets.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>*<sup>5</sup>: For AUTO A/C</ptxt>
